ABUJA  – President Muhammadu Bu­hari has seized the occasion of the 66th birthday of Nigerian industrialist, Aliko Dangote, to pour encomiums on him. Buhari took to a statement by his media aide, Garba She­hu, on Monday, to felicitate with Dangote, describing him as a rare philanthropists who has given new heights to Nigeria’s prestige and global reputation. Buhari wished him a long, healthy life and a joyful year ahead as he clocks 66. “I must commend him for the numerous efforts he is mak­ing for our nation’s progress. “Hearty congratulations and best wishes to the illustri­ous businessman, Aliko Dan­gote, on his birthday. He has given new heights to Nigeria’s prestige and global reputation. May the Almighty give him the strength and wisdom to do even more for the nation,” the pres­ident stated. Buhari Set To Perform Last Official Hajj In Saudi Arabia, Leaves Today Meanwhile, all is now set for President Muhammadu Buhari to travel to Saudi Ara­bia on an official visit, where he is expected to perform the lesser hajj.‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ He is billed to embark on the trip today and return on April 19. POLL A statement by Buhari’s me­dia aide, Garba Shehu, noted that being the president’s last official trip to Saudi Arabia, he will seize the opportunity to perform Umrah, the lesser pilgrimage. He will be accompanied by his aides, the statement added. Buhari is billed to hand over to his successor, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, on May 29, 2023, al­though there are litigations challenging the outcome of the recent presidential elections from opponents. Buhari had at various times stated that he was eager to leave the stage for his successor to en­able him tend to his cattle back home in Daura, Katsina State, where he hails from. To perfect the handing over arrangements, he had inaugu­rated a transition committee prior to the commencement of the 2023 general elections.